&lt;p&gt;The Customer Success Management team at GitLab supports customers across regions by helping them navigate change, improve how they work, and make the most of the GitLab DevSecOps platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a globally distributed, all-remote team, we collaborate asynchronously with Product Management, Engineering, Sales, Professional Services, and other teams to connect customer needs with GitLab’s product and services. We focus on helping customers establish GitLab best practices, including Centers of Excellence, and on using data and customer context to support strategic and technical goals. In APJ, this role helps bring regional perspective to those efforts while working as part of a broader team that values &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;textBold&quot;&gt;collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;textBold&quot;&gt;transparency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;textBold&quot;&gt;results&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. For more on how this team works, see &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong class=&quot;textBold&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/customer-success/csm/segment/&quot;&gt;GitLab’s Customer Success and handbook &lt;/a&gt;resources&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How GitLab Supports Full-Time Employees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/&quot;&gt;Benefits to support your health, finances, and well-being&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
