&lt;p&gt;GitLab is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. GitLab’s policies and practices relating to recruitment, employment, career development and advancement, promotion, and retirement are based solely on merit, regardless of race, color, religion, ancestry, sex (including pregnancy, lactation, sexual orientation, gender identity, or gender expression), national origin, age, citizenship, marital status, mental or physical disability, genetic information (including family medical history), discharge status from the military, protected veteran status (which includes disabled veterans, recently separated veterans, active duty wartime or campaign badge veterans, and Armed Forces service medal veterans), or any other basis protected by law. GitLab will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. See also&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#equal-employment-opportunity-policy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;GitLab’s EEO Policy&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/labor-and-employment-notices/#eeoc-us-equal-employment-opportunity-commission-notices&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;EEO is the Law&lt;/a&gt;. If you have a disability or special need that requires&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#reasonable-accommodation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;accommodation&lt;/a&gt;, please let us know during the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/hiring/interviewing/#adjustments-to-our-interview-process&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;recruiting process&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;GitLab is the intelligent orchestration platform for DevSecOps. GitLab enables organizations to increase developer productivity, improve operational efficiency, reduce security and compliance risk, and accelerate digital transformation. More than 50 million registered users and more than 50% of the Fortune 100* trust GitLab to ship better, more secure software faster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The same principles built into our products are reflected in how our team works: we embrace AI as a core productivity multiplier, with all team members expected to incorporate AI into their daily workflows to drive efficiency, innovation, and impact. GitLab is where careers accelerate, innovation flourishes, and every voice is valued. Our high-performance culture is driven by our values&amp;nbsp;and continuous knowledge exchange, enabling our team members to reach their full potential while collaborating with industry leaders to solve complex problems. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OuZIb5zszQI&quot;&gt;Co-create the future with us&lt;/a&gt; as we build technology that transforms how the world develops software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*&lt;em&gt;Fortune 500® is a registered trademark of Fortune Media IP Limited, used under license. Claim based on GitLab data. Fortune 100 refers to the top 20% ranked companies in the 2025 Fortune 500 list, published in June 2025. Fortune and Fortune Media IP Limited are not affiliated with, and do not endorse products or services of GitLab.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An overview of this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Senior Director, Field CTOs at GitLab, you will lead a small, senior team of Field CTOs while continuing to operate as one yourself. You will help shape the technical voice in GitLab&#39;s most strategic customer conversations, guide how the team engages across regions, and turn what we learn in the field into useful input for sales leadership, product, and marketing. Reporting into go-to-market leadership within the Chief Revenue Officer organization, you will partner closely with the executive teams of GitLab&#39;s largest customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a player-coach role. You will personally engage on GitLab&#39;s most strategic accounts and highest-impact pursuits, while also building, developing, and running a distributed global team. Your time will be split between leading the team and shaping cross-functional strategy, and working directly with customers, executive stakeholders, and external audiences through meetings, events, and written thought leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team works at the intersection of DevSecOps strategy, AI for software development, application security, compliance, and platform modernization. The leaders you and your team advise include Chief Information Security Officers, Chief Security Officers, Chief Technology Officers, chief architects, and leaders in platform engineering and developer productivity. You will serve these leaders by providing clear technical guidance, offering pragmatic recommendations, and communicating tradeoffs transparently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will operate where technology strategy, customer engagement, market leadership, and team development meet. In your first year, you will strengthen the Field CTO operating model, improve how the team is deployed to the highest-value opportunities, and raise the quality and consistency of executive engagement across regions. This is a unique opportunity to help customers understand the value of a single DevSecOps platform while representing GitLab with clarity, transparency, and results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the global Field CTO team by hiring, developing, and retaining senior technical leaders who engage with GitLab&#39;s most strategic customers and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the operating model for the team, including how engagements are scoped, how Field CTOs are matched to accounts and regions, and how insights are documented and shared.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach a team of senior individual contributors through regular one-on-ones, peer review, and clear development plans focused on judgment, executive presence, and strategic impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personally engage as the senior technical voice on a portfolio of GitLab&#39;s most strategic accounts, supporting complex pre-sales motions and executive-level customer relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver thought leadership on DevSecOps, AI for software development, security, compliance, and platform modernization through customer briefings, presentations, events, and written content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with sales leadership, sales engineering, customer success, product, and marketing as a peer to align the Field CTO function with broader go-to-market priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent GitLab externally with analysts, media, and industry audiences, and internally in executive forums where field perspective should help shape company decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curate feedback from the field and turn it into actionable input for product direction, marketing narratives, sales strategy, enablement materials, and reusable technical content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading a senior, customer-facing technical team such as Field CTO, Principal Solutions Architect, Principal Sales Engineer, or Distinguished Engineer, with success developing senior individual contributors across regions and time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong people leadership skills, including hiring, coaching, performance management, and making thoughtful deployment decisions for a highly experienced, executive-facing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience as a technology leader in DevSecOps, application security, information security, or related areas, ideally in roles such as Field CTO, CTO, VP of Engineering, or a comparable executive technical position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated understanding of AI for software development, including how it connects to developer productivity, security, compliance, and enterprise platform strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of software development practices, continuous integration and continuous deployment, cloud and platform architecture, and secure software delivery in enterprise environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive communication skills with the ability to build credibility with senior technology and security leaders, create clear written and verbal points of view, and tailor technical strategy to different audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience representing a company externally through events, analyst conversations, media opportunities, and technical thought leadership content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working autonomously in a fully remote, asynchronous environment, coordinating effectively across time zones, and partnering with stakeholders at the VP level and above.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field CTO organization works across customer-facing and internal teams to help GitLab meet the needs of enterprise organizations with clarity, credibility, and deep technical insight. We partner closely with sales, solutions, marketing, and product stakeholders to represent customer priorities, strengthen technical strategy in the field, and support GitLab&#39;s position in the market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are made up of senior technical leaders who spend much of our time in executive conversations with customers and prospects. Our work often focuses on long-term strategic outcomes rather than short sales cycles, which makes judgment, communication, and careful deployment especially important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success on our team comes from being able to translate complex topics into useful guidance, build trust with senior customer leaders, and help GitLab improve how we serve the market over time. In this role, you will lead experienced operators, stay close to customer reality, and help shape the future of AI-powered DevSecOps at GitLab.&lt;/p&gt;
